{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"366151-all-about-beaks","title":"All About Beaks","description":"Birds have beaks of all kinds, and they use them in many different ways. Dip in.","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"2","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Rohan Dahotre"],"illustrators":["Rohan Dahotre"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Pratham Books","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/366151-all-about-beaks"},"cover":{"card":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/527541/size3/8b9b4ad89f883b4d5fc2428c650116c9.jpg","large":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/527541/size6/8b9b4ad89f883b4d5fc2428c650116c9.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/458586/size6/ed9f0eb9f541184474f7f9a937c70d14.jpg","text":"Drilling beak","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455953/size6/98ea819b519194a183b2224d6e080117.jpg","text":"Fishing beak","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455954/size6/91285d6b1199349c1c991e473c74e94a.jpg","text":"Colourful beak","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455955/size6/2bd9e25b688edae26e29ee5d5c34ee62.jpg","text":"Grain-crushing beak","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455956/size6/a0acc27f1d9bfa16bdd8d5fb6fec9313.jpg","text":"Spoon beak","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455959/size6/2e49cc2261a4beb277ff922dd2304d3e.jpg","text":"Filter beak","words":null},{"n":7,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/458590/size6/0b7150e64247133f5e3d8e2410d03511.jpg","text":"Nutcracker beak","words":null},{"n":8,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455961/size6/9078ea2c381381a145eaca8f923dec77.jpg","text":"Sound-amplifier beak","words":null},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455963/size6/08de4c7d372629f354588534f3db3d29.jpg","text":"Needle beak","words":null},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455964/size6/fa824a07a1502464c0a053eda0913f0f.jpg","text":"Sword beak","words":null},{"n":11,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455965/size6/2bc61056c0b77bb420a12651657ba81f.jpg","text":"Pouch beak","words":null},{"n":12,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455966/size6/c3fb6ebb044f26ef11624283a4e9e99c.jpg","text":"Storage beak","words":null},{"n":13,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455968/size6/326b46bb9a12cbb7c1fee471d7ee6ecf.jpg","text":"More About Beaks\nWoodpeckers have strong, sharp beaks.\nWith these beaks they drill holes in trees to\nmake nests, and also to find insects to eat.\nKingfishers have long, pointed beaks,\nwhich do not disturb the water surface\nwhen they dive in to catch fish.\nToucans use their colourful\nbeaks to show off their beauty\nas well as for self-defence.\nSparrows’ cone-shaped beaks are\nstubby but sharp. They are capable of\ncrushing seeds in a very strong grip.","words":null},{"n":14,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455970/size6/256cc8bf7817f58180c6c0a4f952b1e0.jpg","text":"Spoonbills use their long, flat, rounded\nbeaks to search for fish, amphibians and\ncrabs along the bottom of muddy water.\nFlamingos’ bent beaks help them filter\nout very small plankton, tiny fish and\nfly larvae from shallow, muddy water.\nParrots use their hook-like beaks\nfor cracking open hard nuts.\nHornbills have unique helmet-like structures\non their beaks which help their call travel\nfarther by making the sound boom louder.","words":null},{"n":15,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/455971/size6/4a79ec48b0bad1117c1b69d90888f95a.jpg","text":"Sunbirds have long, curved beaks that point\ndownward. They use their beaks to reach nectar,\nsmall spiders and insects deep inside flowers.\nHummingbirds have very long,\nthin beaks with which they probe\ndeep into flowers for nectar.\nPelicans scoop up fish in their\nbeak pouches. The water drains\nout, and the fish are swallowed.\nPuffins can catch and carry a bunch\nof fish at a time in their beaks.","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":15,"words":240}}